Public key and private key are part of asymmetric encryption, where:

Two keys are generated together
One is shared (public key)
One is kept secret (private key)
🔑 Public Key
Shared openly (can be distributed to anyone)
Used to:
Encrypt data
Verify digital signatures
Cannot be used to decrypt what it encrypts

👉 Example:
If someone wants to send you secure data, they encrypt it using your public key

🔒 Private Key
Kept strictly confidential
Used to:
Decrypt data
Create digital signatures
Must never be exposed

👉 Example:
You decrypt the received data using your private key

🔁 How It Works (Simple Flow)
Sender gets your public key
Encrypts message using public key
Message travels securely over internet
You decrypt using your private key
📌 Interview One-Liner

“Public key is used for encryption and sharing, while private key is used for decryption
and must be kept secret. Together they enable secure communication using asymmetric encryption.”

🔥 Real-Time DevOps / AWS Usage
SSH Login (EC2)
Public key stored in EC2
Private key used from your system
SSL/TLS (HTTPS)
Public key in certificate
Private key on server
IAM / KMS / Secrets
Used for encryption/decryption of sensitive data

